SIMPLE: gemmation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gemmation
<hw>Gem*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>gemmation</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The formation of a new
individual, either animal or vegetable, by a process of budding; an
asexual method of reproduction; gemmulation; gemmiparity. See
<er>Budding</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The arrangement of buds on the
stalk; also, of leaves in the bud.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gemmeous</ent>⟦br⟧
